>> Here's more about the DJs:
>>
>> DJ Hil Huerta (CaliGrown, Skillz, OPPSF) was introduced to
>> club music in
>> the early 80's by his cousin, Eddie Garcia (aka Eddie
>> Def).  He began
>> DJing on a set of used decks when he was 11 years old. By
>> 1986, while
>> still in middle school, Hil had begun throwing and
>> promoting parties,
>> playing a mix of freestyle, hip hop, and early house music.
>> Hil's drive
>> and love of dance music has not abated.  Now one of the Bay
>> Area's top
>> promoters and still a top-notch DJ, Hil is know for his
>> eclectic house
>> music sets, ranging from funky cuts to electro-fueled tech
>> house to
>> progressive grooves.  Of course, says Hil, "I still
>> have all of my old
>> stuff, so you never know when I might throw in something
>> classic."
>>
>> Of course, all of this musical diversity serves a purpose.
>> While some
>> DJ's will play a singular type of music to a crowd
>> that's not enjoying
>> it, Hil has a deeper appreciation for dancers and wants to
>> make sure
>> everyone has a good time.  As he says "I play every
>> level of house
>> music, just to keep the crowd moving." In his
>> continuing quest to keep
>> the crowd moving, Hil divides his time between DJing,
>> running a
>> successful promotions company, and work in the studio.  He
>> is currently
>> producing music with Homero Espinosa of Yerba Buena Discos.
>>
>> DJ Hil's notable residences & bookings include Club
>> 1015 (SF), Space 550
>> (SF), Ultra Music Festival (Miami); Lovefest (and
>> "Love" in SF).
>>
>> Chuck.G, co-founder of CaliGrown Events, first learned to
>> DJ in Dean's
>> garage over 10 years ago. Although he hasn't pursued
>> DJ'ing as a
>> full-time career, music has been a lifelong passion for
>> Chuck. He sums
>> up this passion with the following statement: "My
>> first rave was in
>> Germany, during a High School exchange visit in the
>> 'early' 90's.  I
>> walked in, and that was it."
>>
>> Chuck's passion for music has driven him to DJ,
>> produce, and promote
>> underground music events under different names &
>> aliases his entire
>> adult life. Chuck's more notable gigs include opening
>> for Filter Grinder
>> (Bush Records) in North Hollywood in 2002, and a residennce
>> at the now
>> infamous Club Ibiza in 2001, being billed with such acts as
>> DJ Keoki,
>> Dirty Vegas, and even MTV's DJ Scribble (Although Chuck
>> jokes about how
>> small his name was in print, and how the first time he was
>> mistakenly
>> billed as DJ "G-huck.G"- a name that has stuck
>> with his friends).
>> Although Chuck claims he sold his soul to House, he is
>> never afraid to
>> step outside of the box and drop some raw sh!t. Therefore,
>> he classifies
>> himself as a "party DJ" instead of limiting his
>> scope to one genre.
>>
>> DJ Dean Kroh (CaliGrown, Seedling Music, Liquid Graf-X) is
>> one mean
>> breaks DJ. Hailing from Stockton (holla!) Dean's been
>> rocking dance
>> floors since 1996 with some raw tracks you ain't never
>> heard! With too
>> many notable gigs to list, let's just say he's been
>> doin' this since
>> HomeBase was a Nu-skool spot, ya heard!?!?
>>
>> So that's what to expect!  Hope to have you listening!

I'd say figure out a cpu that's compatible with the mobo and buy that.
Likely it'll be a slightly less powerful sort, but it'd be by far the
cheaper component to replace. But then again, maybe not, if you look hard
enough you can find a decent mobo for > 100 bucks. Really it shouldn't
matter which you replace, but my first instinct would be to replace the cpu
since that's probably cheaper and definitely easier from an effort
standpoint.

So what I'd do if I was in your shoes is find a decent cpu to replace the
incompatible one, maybe sell that one on ebay or something, or maybe build
another system around it. I wouldn't worry about the error messages, most
likely they won't cause any permanent damage. Also, could you post the
actual message that's coming up? That'd go a long way in making this
clearer.

Subject: RE: [sfraves] Calling all compugeek heads... help?

Hey Dragn'fly,

Smitty from the Moksha Tribe here to help with your tech conundrum. First
great choice on the motherboard. I love Asus and have used thier MBs for
over a decade now. I believe you should hang on to the hardware you have and
ask any friends if they have a Socket775 processor you can borrow to update
your bios.

The current bios version for that board is 1013 (I'm guessing you have an
older bios version):

http://dlsvr01.asus.com/pub/ASUS/mb/socket775/P5K-E/P5KE1013.zip

I read one review on Newegg that said:

"got the board was old bios version, did not reconigzed the Q6600 CPU, End
up I have to get one of old CPU to run it and update the bios then put back
the Q6600. Little bit of work arround but finally the system up and runing
as it should."

You also have a Q-series CPU and the bios updates that Asus lists show many
updates to include some of the new processors. I say dont swap the hardware
and put an extra 15mins of work into updating the bios so the hardware
combination you bought will work (again you will just need to borrow another
socket775 cpu to do that 5mins of work to updated it). You can see which
CPUs your MB supports for which the cooresponding bios versions here:

http://support.asus.com/cpusupport/cpusupport.aspx

Yours is listed to be supported after the 1012 version...so update that bios
and you will be good to go! And Pinko is right, dont worry about a
'meltdown'...the MBs are designed to protect themselves against incompatible
CPUs and thus why only a bios update is required to get it going (issue
resides in software not hardware layer).

On a side note I am finished mastering the Phoenix party audio but I need
your help in identifying where you started playing after Forest's set.
Please email me back privately and I will forward you the master audio file
links so you can tell me which time you came in.

-Smitty

meltdlown of any components?

suggestions you have for me?

On Fri, May 23, 2008 at 7:52 AM, Ryan Smith <sf_smith@comcast.net> =
wrote:

> Hey Dragn'fly,
>
> Smitty from the Moksha Tribe here to help with your tech conundrum. =
First
> great choice on the motherboard. I love Asus and have used thier MBs =
for
> over a decade now. I believe you should hang on to the hardware you =
have
> and
> ask any friends if they have a Socket775 processor you can borrow to =
update
> your bios.
>
> The current bios version for that board is 1013 (I'm guessing you have =
an
> older bios version):
>
> http://dlsvr01.asus.com/pub/ASUS/mb/socket775/P5K-E/P5KE1013.zip
>
> I read one review on Newegg that said:
>
> "got the board was old bios version, did not reconigzed the Q6600 CPU, =
End
> up I have to get one of old CPU to run it and update the bios then put =
back
> the Q6600. Little bit of work arround but finally the system up and =
runing
> as it should."
>
> You also have a Q-series CPU and the bios updates that Asus lists show =
many
> updates to include some of the new processors. I say dont swap the =
hardware
> and put an extra 15mins of work into updating the bios so the hardware
> combination you bought will work (again you will just need to borrow
> another
> socket775 cpu to do that 5mins of work to updated it). You can see =
which
> CPUs your MB supports for which the cooresponding bios versions here:
>
> http://support.asus.com/cpusupport/cpusupport.aspx
>
> Yours is listed to be supported after the 1012 version...so update =
that
> bios
> and you will be good to go! And Pinko is right, dont worry about a
> 'meltdown'...the MBs are designed to protect themselves against
> incompatible
> CPUs and thus why only a bios update is required to get it going =
(issue
> resides in software not hardware layer).
>
> On a side note I am finished mastering the Phoenix party audio but I =
need
> your help in identifying where you started playing after Forest's set.
> Please email me back privately and I will forward you the master audio =
file
> links so you can tell me which time you came in.
>
> -Smitty

On Fri, May 23, 2008 at 07:52:43AM -0700, Ryan Smith wrote:
> Hey Dragn'fly,
> 
> Smitty from the Moksha Tribe here to help with your tech conundrum. First
> great choice on the motherboard. I love Asus and have used thier MBs for
> over a decade now. I believe you should hang on to the hardware you have and
> ask any friends if they have a Socket775 processor you can borrow to update
> your bios.
> 
> The current bios version for that board is 1013 (I'm guessing you have an
> older bios version):
> 
> http://dlsvr01.asus.com/pub/ASUS/mb/socket775/P5K-E/P5KE1013.zip
> 
> I read one review on Newegg that said:
> 
> "got the board was old bios version, did not reconigzed the Q6600 CPU, End
> up I have to get one of old CPU to run it and update the bios then put back
> the Q6600. Little bit of work arround but finally the system up and runing
> as it should."
> 
> You also have a Q-series CPU and the bios updates that Asus lists show many
> updates to include some of the new processors. I say dont swap the hardware
> and put an extra 15mins of work into updating the bios so the hardware
> combination you bought will work (again you will just need to borrow another
> socket775 cpu to do that 5mins of work to updated it). You can see which
> CPUs your MB supports for which the cooresponding bios versions here:
> 
> http://support.asus.com/cpusupport/cpusupport.aspx
> 
> Yours is listed to be supported after the 1012 version...so update that bios
> and you will be good to go! And Pinko is right, dont worry about a
> 'meltdown'...the MBs are designed to protect themselves against incompatible
> CPUs and thus why only a bios update is required to get it going (issue
> resides in software not hardware layer).
> 
> On a side note I am finished mastering the Phoenix party audio but I need
> your help in identifying where you started playing after Forest's set.
> Please email me back privately and I will forward you the master audio file
> links so you can tell me which time you came in.
> 
> -Smitty
>

From: Brandon High [mailto:bhigh@freaks.com]=20
Sent: Thursday, May 22, 2008 8:40 PM
To: Dragn'fly
Subject: Re: Fw: [sfraves] Calling all compugeek heads... help?

My wife asked me if I knew the answers for what you're asking, so here
goes:

First off, have you checked the feedback on Newegg to see if someone
else has run into the same issue?

> 1)      Should I hold onto my CPU / mobo and hope the mobo comes out
> with a bios update that recognizes it?

It looks like bios 1012 supports it, according to
http://support.asus.com/cpusupport/cpusupport.aspx - The latest BIOS
is 1013.

> 3)      The comp still runs seemingly fine to me (although I've yet to
> run it at any real length of time on account of my paranoia with such
> messages) but if I do run it, despite the conflict =96 am I risking a
> meltdlown of any components?

The voltage might be too high, since the chip was not recognized.
Flashing the BIOS should take care of it. You can also check or change
voltage settings in the bios or with the ASUS utility if you're
worried.

> 4)      =85 any other things I should be worried about, looked into or
> suggestions you have for me?

> + a gigabyte fanless 8600 + other stuff if you need me to disclose=85

You might want to get an aftermarket CPU cooler, they're usually
quieter and work better. Since the video card doesn't have a fan, it's
going to dump heat into the case and possibly make the CPU fan work
harder.

I have a (gigantic) Zalman 9700 on my system and it's very, very
quiet. There are smaller heat sinks that work well, too.

-B

Brandon High                                        bhigh@freaks.com

I did check the link that B had provided before and found that my CPU gained
support with version 1012 and now it's up to 1013 so seems it should
recognize it.  I've yet to find out how to determine which version of bios
I'm running. So far I've gotten the hardware list to pop up during boot up,
but I'm still working on the BIOS thingamajigger...

As for the actual message I get once it's all booted up is: "Unknown CPU is
detected, updating BIOS is required to unleash it's full power! Press F1 to
Resume".  Oh and on the top left corner it has a logo: American Megatrends,
www.ami.com

Hopefully the guy who built it was just in a hurry and didn't update with
the latest BIOS but again I'm still working on finding which version I got
on there.  I'll keep at it...

other than that, it does run like a charm and at least to me seems smokin'
fast!  My post up here was more out of paranoia of running it w/o it
recognizing the cpu (didn't want it to cause random overheating due to
random issues with the cpu unknown or cause a random burnout...) although
the message given to me doesn't make me run out and panic.... quite yet.

; )
d
----- Original Message ----- 
From: "pinkko" <ealaughlin@gmail.com>
To: "SFR" <sfraves@hyperreal.org>
Sent: Friday, May 23, 2008 7:19 AM
Subject: Re: [sfraves] Calling all compugeek heads... help?


I'd say figure out a cpu that's compatible with the mobo and buy that.
Likely it'll be a slightly less powerful sort, but it'd be by far the
cheaper component to replace. But then again, maybe not, if you look hard
enough you can find a decent mobo for > 100 bucks. Really it shouldn't
matter which you replace, but my first instinct would be to replace the cpu
since that's probably cheaper and definitely easier from an effort
standpoint.

So what I'd do if I was in your shoes is find a decent cpu to replace the
incompatible one, maybe sell that one on ebay or something, or maybe build
another system around it. I wouldn't worry about the error messages, most
likely they won't cause any permanent damage. Also, could you post the
actual message that's coming up? That'd go a long way in making this
clearer.

----- Original Message ----- 
From: "Ryan Smith" <sf_smith@comcast.net>
To: <sfraves@hyperreal.org>
Sent: Friday, May 23, 2008 7:52 AM
Subject: RE: [sfraves] Calling all compugeek heads... help?


> Hey Dragn'fly,
>
> Smitty from the Moksha Tribe here to help with your tech conundrum. First
> great choice on the motherboard. I love Asus and have used thier MBs for
> over a decade now. I believe you should hang on to the hardware you have 
> and
> ask any friends if they have a Socket775 processor you can borrow to 
> update
> your bios.
>
> The current bios version for that board is 1013 (I'm guessing you have an
> older bios version):
>
> http://dlsvr01.asus.com/pub/ASUS/mb/socket775/P5K-E/P5KE1013.zip
>
> I read one review on Newegg that said:
>
> "got the board was old bios version, did not reconigzed the Q6600 CPU, End
> up I have to get one of old CPU to run it and update the bios then put 
> back
> the Q6600. Little bit of work arround but finally the system up and runing
> as it should."
>
> You also have a Q-series CPU and the bios updates that Asus lists show 
> many
> updates to include some of the new processors. I say dont swap the 
> hardware
> and put an extra 15mins of work into updating the bios so the hardware
> combination you bought will work (again you will just need to borrow 
> another
> socket775 cpu to do that 5mins of work to updated it). You can see which
> CPUs your MB supports for which the cooresponding bios versions here:
>
> http://support.asus.com/cpusupport/cpusupport.aspx
>
> Yours is listed to be supported after the 1012 version...so update that 
> bios
> and you will be good to go! And Pinko is right, dont worry about a
> 'meltdown'...the MBs are designed to protect themselves against 
> incompatible
> CPUs and thus why only a bios update is required to get it going (issue
> resides in software not hardware layer).
>
> On a side note I am finished mastering the Phoenix party audio but I need
> your help in identifying where you started playing after Forest's set.
> Please email me back privately and I will forward you the master audio 
> file
> links so you can tell me which time you came in.
>
> -Smitty
>

Subject: Re: [sfraves] Calling all compugeek heads... help?

On Fri, May 23, 2008 at 12:24:19PM -0700, Dragn'fly wrote:
> I did check the link that B had provided before and found that my CPU gained
> support with version 1012 and now it's up to 1013 so seems it should
> recognize it.  I've yet to find out how to determine which version of bios
> I'm running. So far I've gotten the hardware list to pop up during boot up,
> but I'm still working on the BIOS thingamajigger...
> 
> As for the actual message I get once it's all booted up is: "Unknown CPU is
> detected, updating BIOS is required to unleash it's full power! Press F1 to
> Resume".  Oh and on the top left corner it has a logo: American Megatrends,
> www.ami.com

Should tell you the bios version along with a build date/timestamp during that
same point.  There's generally never harm in reloading BIOS so I'd suggest
just grabbing the latest and installing it(just make sure you grab the
correct one for your botherboard!).

You may need to go into the bios settings, and enable extended boot messages
or disable quick boot, but in general they all still support listing the
bios version and date as the first text on bootup (well, after the video
card does its thing, sometimes that'll come up as video initializes, THEN
display the BIOS stuff just before it covers it up with the silly graphics
while it boots.


Ray


> 
> Hopefully the guy who built it was just in a hurry and didn't update with
> the latest BIOS but again I'm still working on finding which version I got
> on there.  I'll keep at it...
> 
> other than that, it does run like a charm and at least to me seems smokin'
> fast!  My post up here was more out of paranoia of running it w/o it
> recognizing the cpu (didn't want it to cause random overheating due to
> random issues with the cpu unknown or cause a random burnout...) although
> the message given to me doesn't make me run out and panic.... quite yet.
> 
> ; )
> d
> ----- Original Message ----- 
> From: "pinkko" <ealaughlin@gmail.com>
> To: "SFR" <sfraves@hyperreal.org>
> Sent: Friday, May 23, 2008 7:19 AM
> Subject: Re: [sfraves] Calling all compugeek heads... help?
> 
> 
> I'd say figure out a cpu that's compatible with the mobo and buy that.
> Likely it'll be a slightly less powerful sort, but it'd be by far the
> cheaper component to replace. But then again, maybe not, if you look hard
> enough you can find a decent mobo for > 100 bucks. Really it shouldn't
> matter which you replace, but my first instinct would be to replace the cpu
> since that's probably cheaper and definitely easier from an effort
> standpoint.
> 
> So what I'd do if I was in your shoes is find a decent cpu to replace the
> incompatible one, maybe sell that one on ebay or something, or maybe build
> another system around it. I wouldn't worry about the error messages, most
> likely they won't cause any permanent damage. Also, could you post the
> actual message that's coming up? That'd go a long way in making this
> clearer.
>

unknown, in recognition of 10 years of M_nus, this month FAKTION brings you
a lineup of 3 headliners.  That's right, no opening acts,and we've really
got DRUMCELL coming here to help get you moving on the dance floor!
Recently, he and DJ DEVELOPER have been touring together, representing
LA Techno the world over, and they've decided to drop by together for
some fun in San Francisco.  As if these SoCal powerhouses weren't enough,
our own FOREST GREEN makes the night right with 2 hours of techno madness!

After Drumcell completes his set, we can walk the 3 short blocks to catch
Ritchie Hawtin (see the Blasthaus site for details; it's a separate
party with a separate cover) at 1015 Folsom/103 Harriet.


Friday, 30 May 2008

F A K T I O N : because san francisco needs another techno cult

Friday, 30 May 2008:

Last Fridays @ Anu

DRUMCELL: Founder of Droid Recordings and co-founder of LA's Droid
Behavior with Acid Circus, Drumcell's energetic and frenetic take on
minimal put LA on the global map and always wins crowds over.  He's
played all over the world and remains the standard bearer for techno
in Southern California.

DEVELOPER: DJ Developer is known throughout the US, Mexico and abroad
for quick mixing abilities and for leading LA's second wave of Techno.
Most recently, he and longtime friend Drumcell have been touring together, 
just like they're doing right here for you.

FOREST GREEN:  In the bleakest days of San Francisco techno, you could
always count on Forest to bring out totally dope techno, whether in a
mainstream setting, undergrounds or any other place in the world.  Sure,
she's got the talent to pay the bills with balls-out electro, breaks,
dubstep beats, and nearly anything else, she's also got the heart to
consistently deliver techno madness.  We have no idea what she'll play
or if she'll pull out vinyl, cd, or even jam a live set, we're just sure
we'll love it and so will you!

Subject: [sfraves] VOTE NO ON PROPOSITION 98

>From a housing rights lawyer-friend.

---------- Forwarded message ----------

PLEASE everyone VOTE against the blatant BS.

Tell everyone you know that they must VOTE NO on 98.

Guess what?  The rest of the state is going to vote yes on the 
proposition because they hate SF, Berkeley and Oakland!  There are only 
handful of cities where rent control exists.  Many people who own small 
buildings in the bay area live in hate the bay area parts of the state 
and have been telling everyone for years how terrible it is that they 
are stuck with you in their building.....and you are screwed...guess 
what else?

I have represented so many families and individuals facing losing their 
homes in San Francisco for 15 years while rent control has been in full 
force and effect because any sophisticated landlord can evict you right 
now.

The idiots proposing this sham eminent domain initiative make statements 
that there is a housing shortage because landlords are afraid to build 
new apartment buildings.

They forgot to mention that rent control only provides protection to 
buildings that are over 30 years old and which are qualified!

They forgot to mention the 6.14 notice, which landlords served on you 
years ago that says when the original renter moves out, the landlord can 
adjust the rent to far market value.  The remaining roommates have to 
pay up or go!

They also forgot to mention SF Admin Code, Chapter 37, Section 
37.9(a)(13).  Attorneys for landlords throw that in my face all the 
time!!!  A faceless trustee of a revocable living trust will buy your 
building and retain an attorney to give you 120 days and $4,748.40 
relocation fees.  They are resentful they have to do that much.  There 
are only limited procedural defenses to an Ellis act eviction.

Speaking of chapter and verse, what about SF Admin Code, Chapter 37, 
Section 37.9(a)(8)?  OMI is what we call them.  Owners can move in with 
60 days notice!  What is an owner?  You mean all the revocable living 
trust has to do is put together 5 pages of documents forming a family 
trust and two more pages transferring 25% ownership to that trust and 
your good to go!!!!! It cant be that easy!!!!

What about sections 9,10,11 and 12.  Substantial rehabilitation! capital 
improvements!! Wait, I forgot, we won the condo conversion lottery!!

What about evictions for all those lease violations....the subletting 
without permission, the hamster, the constant late payment of rent, the 
parties, the business activity, the illegal activity....OUT OUT OUT!!!!

And what if you receive a notice of eviction?  Few attorneys will defend 
an unlawful detainer action (eviction) because the average renter cannot 
gamble that kind of money if they are faced with incurring moving 
expenses and increased rent and security deposits.  Tenants have few 
rights under the current state of the law and few of those have the 
resources or wherewithal to fight for their rights.

Organizations like The SF Tenants Union, the Eviction Defense 
Collaborative, La Raza and The Tenderloin Housing Clinic are invaluable 
resources, assisting tenants who cannot afford private counsel.  They 
have useful information on their websites describing the all out efforts 
by the "oppressed" landlords to get rid of everyone who is not 
financially well off.

Attorneys fighting for renter's homes need more tools not less.  Please 
vote no on 98.

p.s.


IF YOU DON'T LIKE RENT CONTROL, DON'T BUY A BUILDING SUBJECT TO THE 
STATUTE.  BUY SOMETHING ELSE. THERE ARE PLENTY OF OTHER INVESTMENT 
OPPORTUNITIES HERE IN SAN FRANCISCO.  IF YOU ARE A LANDLORD AND YOU FEEL 
YOU ARE BEING CHEATED OUT OF FAIR MARKET VALUE RENTS.  SELL YOUR 
BUILDING TO SOMEONE WHO IS NOT AS OUT OF IT AS YOU AND YOU WILL MAKE A 
FORTUNE.  THEN YOU CAN LEAVE SF.  PLEASE LEAVE BAY AREA RENTERS IN PEACE 
IN THEIR HOMES.

[A]n RFID tag fitted to the customer's bank card or passbook could be
used to signal their arrival at a branch.  As they pass through the
doors, the card would alert a customer information system.  Bank staff
could personally greet high-net-wealth customers, or customers could
be greeted by name by tellers, who would already have their account
information on-screen when they arrive at the counter.

website, available at IBM.com (October 7, 2004).

Friday I saw all four of The Fingermonsters playing together for (my) first time since their OW debut. It goes without saying they rocked it proper! Sorry I forgot my record AGAIN Marco, my bad! Oh yeah, sup Alex!
   
  Sorry we didn't catch up on Sat., Terry, I went in there hella times but I know you were busy, ;) !  :P  BIG UP'S to the visuals though, seriously. You guys took that room to another level.  
   
  I spent MAYBE a total of 10 minutes in the main room @ ETD, just for spectacle's sake (and it was one, I will grant Skills that), however most of my night was over in the house/breaks partition. Dan & Donald were rockin some nasty & funky electro sh1t right around one, just as the power went out in the middle of their set. In retrospect, I ALMOST wish I could have seen the power go out in the middle of Tiesto's set, but I'm confident I was in the best spot when it all went down. We got to the car (and the F11K out of there) seconds before the big rush.
   
  Saw some girls run into the divider on the 101 on the way home, cut across all the lanes, then stall in the right lane. So Bryce, J-Bar & I stopped and threw a couple flares out for them. Next one of them (the driver, I think) asked me if she could tell the cops she was with us and not in the car. Around that time, Bryce & J-Bar pointed out I didn't exactly appear 'Mr. Sober' myself, so we told them sorry time for us to peace the f11k out. Glad you're OK, C-YA!
   
  BTW, on a side note, Justice is f'n huge now I see. Props to Eric for calling that one so early; if you're out there somewhere reading this.
   
  peace
   
  chuck

On Tue, 27 May 2008, CHUCK G wrote:
>  Sorry we didn't catch up on Sat., Terry, I went in there 
> hella times but I know you were busy, ;) !   :P  BIG UP'S to 
> the visuals though, seriously. You guys took that room to 
> another level.

Thanks :-) So yeah I spent all day and most of the night at 
Skills etd.POP. I really do like massives...if I'm doing visuals 
for them.

But this time I was assigned the hardcore room, and while the 
production was huge (lasers,lighting, sound-wise), I couldn't 
stay in there longer for 15-20mins at a time. So yeah I kept 
missing you Chuck (we were texting the whole night). Luckily I 
had the 2.0 crew to tagteam the visuals setup.

If anyone cares, Skills ended an hour early because a 
transformer blew, and there was quite an undercover sting going 
on, where undercovers as candy ravers were popping people left 
and right. Kinda crazy to watch happen.

There was a small word of mouth Moksha Tribe crew-type-party the 
same night I hit up afterwards, super fun to just lay back and 
chill.

The whole weekend Paula & I were calulated what exactly we'd be 
doing if we made the trip up to OODE this year, this is the 
2nd(?) one we've missed in the last 10 years.

-terry

I've seen a number of undercover operations, even from the old 
Homebase 85th/Baldwin days. And yes, this last weekend was 
quite a bit more orchestrated/aggressive, and their candy kid 
outfits a lot more elaborate. I had backstage access so I could 
follow people through as they were getting processed. There 
were a number of processing rooms, unmarked small ones in the 
hallways, and a larger one backstage.

Big pants, tons of glo-wear, candy bracelets, They all looked 
to be in their mid 20's. Alhtough I also heard they used young 
looking candy girls as bait/scouts.

Was weird to watch as they would inconspicuously grab an 
unsuspecting offender and muscle them through the arena to one 
of the processing rooms, then they were transported backstage 
and out the back to the police station.

I should also point out the number of arrests were about the 
same as the last 2 Coolworld events there in 2003 and 2004...60 
people.

-t

I heard there were over 1000+ felony "charges" brought forth from arrests on Sat. 




dangrsmind@yahoo.com wrote: There's a subtle difference which Michael is indicating I think.
Undercover work implies that the person has specilized training.  Most narcotics officers are not undercover agents, although they may very well have some undercover training. Undercover work is a very specific specialty and there really aren't that many undercover agents.  Using them is a sort of a big deal since it can also blow their cover.  
Undercover agents are not used at most of the events in SF I've been to.  Usually its just someone who is clearly a cop that comes up and asks for pills or whatever.  They wait until after the bar closes and start approaching the wasted looking people that are still left.
The article reporting the bust states that "115 police officers and support personnel from about 20 law enforcement agencies" were involved.  That seems to be an awful lot of muscle even for a medium sized massive.
I sense a disturbance in the force...be careful out there guys.
Best,
Peter

Well from experience, many county or cities have agencies that are put=20
together for making bust in our scene and an event like this was easy=20
pickings. If there are no bust these agencies fail and lose funding.=20
This why they had come out in full force at the skills event along with=20
very young recruits.  At the coolworld events they were dressed in=20
street clothes and not rave atire. Also they did not look younger that=20
40 years old.

The guys that went to the clubs in DC were typically very plain looking - l=
ike, they could blend in with just about any crowd. Typically Early to mid =
20's - sometimes preppy, sometimes clubby, never looked like cops.=20

At Raves though, they ran the gamut of looks, up to and including candy rav=
ers.=20

The bottom line - don't buy drugs from folks you don't know or sell drugs t=
o people you don't know. And when possible, don't involve money in drug tra=
nsactions - give 'em all to me for free!

;p

Subject: [sfraves] BSP: Jovino on An Epiphany Of Sound tomorrow

I'll be hosting long time DJ Jovino on An Epiphany Of Sound tomorrow, 
from 9a to Noon.  He originally began DJing under the name "car bomb" 
back in the '80s, playing mostly new wave and punk.   He then took a 
rather long hiatus, and came back into the fold, playing a rather 
eclectic mix of music at campouts and house parties on his laptop.
More recently, he's been focusing more on dance music as well as setting 
aside his laptop in favor of CDs.

Currently, he's the resident for Nerd Salon, has been a guest DJ in 
clubs such as The Fencesitter's Ball and most recently F*ck S4it Let's 
Dance (FSLD), and he also has a regular show on Theory Radio 
(http://theoryradio.org/) every Wednesday from 12-noon to 2pm.

Listen in for him tomorrow on 90.1 FM in the Bay Area, as well as online 
at http://kzsulive.stanford.edu .   He'll also be making a return 
appearance ahead of his gig for Pink Saturday on June 28th, which will 
be in front of the Bank of America in the Castro.

I'm hoping you won't miss out on tomorrow, but there will be another 
chance to catch him real soon in case you do!

Be happy.

may also have visual components by then, but that's very far from
guaranteed. if you're there this year, check it out. I'm actually
going very much with the old-school ambient mafia philosophy, because
BM has lots and lots of music, but it could definitely do with some
quieting down and chilling out.

Subject: [sfraves] [BSP] Re: HAWTIN ON FRIDAY :: Peace, love, harmony




On Thu, May 29, 2008 at 02:38:21AM -0700, electrofunk138@hotmail.com wrote:
> 
> Fuck Hawtin....Drumcell, Developer and Forest Green @ Faktion Friday night (Anu) !!!!

Much gratitude for the endorsement.  And yes, speaking of Faktion, we've just
added a new visuals crew: HEROIC ROBOT.  If we can get the laser mounted
usefully they've got some amazing shit programmed in lately.


Yes, ONE MORE DAY:

On their return from DEMF, Chicago, Guadalajara Mexico and great parties
unknown, in recognition of 10 years of M_nus, this month FAKTION brings you
a lineup of 3 headliners.  That's right, no opening acts,and we've really
got DRUMCELL coming here to help get you moving on the dance floor!
Recently, he and DJ DEVELOPER have been touring together, representing
LA Techno the world over, and they've decided to drop by together for
some fun in San Francisco.  As if these SoCal powerhouses weren't enough,
our own FOREST GREEN makes the night right with 2 hours of techno madness!
Just added: Visuals by HEROIC ROBOT!

After Drumcell completes his set, we can walk the 3 short blocks to catch
Ritchie Hawtin (see the Blasthaus site for details; it's a separate
party with a separate cover) at 1015 Folsom/103 Harriet.


Friday, 30 May 2008

RAY presents: 

F A K T I O N : because san francisco needs another techno cult
with special guests:

Friday, 30 May 2008:
DRUMCELL: Droid Behavior/Omniscient [ LA ]
DEVELOPER: Modularz/Sound Division [ LA ]
FOREST GREEN: Cute Fang Recordings/Cute Things With Fangs/ForestGreen.org/Daly City Records/Faktion [ SF ]

Visuals: HEROIC ROBOT [ SF ]

Last Fridays @ Anu

DRUMCELL: Founder of Droid Recordings and co-founder of LA's Droid
Behavior with Acid Circus, Drumcell's energetic and frenetic take on
minimal put LA on the global map and always wins crowds over.  He's
played all over the world and remains the standard bearer for techno
in Southern California.

DEVELOPER: DJ Developer is known throughout the US, Mexico and abroad
for quick mixing abilities and for leading LA's second wave of Techno.
Most recently, he and longtime friend Drumcell have been touring together, 
just like they're doing right here for you.

FOREST GREEN:  In the bleakest days of San Francisco techno, you could
always count on Forest to bring out totally dope techno, whether in a
mainstream setting, undergrounds or any other place in the world.  Sure,
she's got the talent to pay the bills with balls-out electro, breaks,
dubstep beats, and nearly anything else, she's also got the heart to
consistently deliver techno madness.  We have no idea what she'll play
or if she'll pull out vinyl, cd, or even jam a live set, we're just sure
we'll love it and so will you!
 


Anu-Bar 
43 Sixth St., San Francisco, CA
10 PM to 2 AM 21+
Cost: $5, free b4 11pm, females free b4 midnight

Official Site: http://www.faktionsf.com/

 
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Other parties of interest:
Our friends at Killswitch continue their weekly Friday happy hour techno
set of goodness at UndergroundSF (424 Haight at Webster), 6-10pm.  Prior
to this month's FAKTION, in addition to residents dcoy and jav8, they've
got Christian Schmidt and The Worker from fiction along with cheap drinks
($4 will get you a Stella and a slice of pizza from 6-7).  No Cover.

Blasthaus is hosting the official M_nus party the same night, as mentioned,
so once Drumcell kills it many of us will walk together the 3 blocks to
1015 Folsom/103 Harriet, to catch headliner Ritchie Hawtin.  $25, you may
want to purchase in advance to save time at the door.

On June 6, Radio Integrated and DEFSF are opening their doors for an
all night loft party.  This is a special, Limited Capacity party, check
in with Radio Integrated and DEF for details.

On June 7, [KONTROL] celebrates their 3 year anniversary at the Endup
with guests Radio Slave, Par Grindvik and local favorite Monty Luke.
10pm-6am, $15 after 11.


///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
 
Coming up: Faktion: Last Fridays @ Anu 
Friday, 27 June 2008:
DISCONNECT: DEF/blissfactory [ Oakland ]
TORO TORO: friends&family/faktion [ SF|Oakland ]

Subject: [sfraves] BSP:  <BRASS TAX> WWOD?  Golden Gate Park, this Saturday May 31st!

--Apple-Mail-1--274295286
Content-Type: text/plain;
	charset=ISO-8859-1;
	format=flowed;
	delsp=yes
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

A large void has been left in our lives due to the passing of our dear
friend Otto Schutt.  Let's gather this Saturday to fill that void with
sunshine, smiles, hugs, music, dancing, and a liberal helping of
shenanigans.  We'll celebrate Otto's life by coming together to share
all of the things he loved.  Just ask yourself, "What Would Otto Do?"
He wouldn't want us moping around right now - he'd want us living out
loud, shaking our asses and making each other laugh.  So BRING IT!

The celebration will be in Elk Glen Picnic Area in Golden Gate Park
(directions below) beginning at noon and going until at least 6,
probably later.  There are picnic tables and grills there, and we'll
have charcoal and some camp stoves for makin' bacon.  Kids are
definitely welcome - we'll even have a bouncy castle for them (and for
adults too of course).  Dogs are also welcome, but they should probably
stay out of the bouncy castle.

We will be creating an altar on the dance floor in honor of Otto. Please
feel free to bring photos, fabric, effigies, memories, writings, relics,
flowers or anything that you might want to contribute to keep his
presence with us.  If you would like to help with the creation of the
altar, please contact Babs (babsicali@gmail.com) and Jess
(jess_stockton@yahoo.com).

A full stable of Brass Tax DJs will be bumping tunes to help you do your
best Otto dance, but you are also welcome to contribute any special song
that you would like to hear in honor of the big man.  There are a couple
ways you can do this:

1. Bring a cd, record, or ipod with you on Saturday and give it to
DingDong.  Make sure it is well labeled with the specific song you want
to have played, along with your name and phone number so we can get it
back to you if it gets mixed in with other music.

2. Email an mp3 to DingDong at dingdong@gmail.com.  We'll be setting up
all Saturday morning so make sure you send it to him by Friday.

We do however have a full lineup already, including a couple BTx
residents flying in from afar, so please keep it to one or two songs.
You can trust that the BTx is very familiar with Otto's expansive taste
in music and it will certainly be represented to the fullest!

We'll also be doing a sing-along of Paul's song "Love on Ottomatic."
The lyrics are printed below, under the directions to the park, but
we'll also have some copies printed out.

If you have any other ideas or ways you would like to contribute, please
feel free!  This is everyone's celebration - not just a Brass Tax party.
If you want some help or have questions, contact Stefanie at
sgesiorski@yahoo.com.

We know some of you on this list never had the opportunity to meet Otto,
but you are still more than welcome to come - you'll hear so many great
stories you'll feel like you know him!

Please forward this email far and wide so it reaches everyone it needs
to.

GIVE THANKS!!!

Putting our love on Otto-matic,
Brass Tax

DIRECTIONS TO ELK GLEN PICNIC AREA:

Ride your bike, take MUNI, or carpool!

 =46rom Bay Bridge (I-80): Once on Fell Street, continue to Kezar Drive =
to
Lincoln Way. Continue down Lincoln Way to 25th Avenue. Turn right on
25th Avenue into Golden Gate Park. Make a left on Martin Luther King Jr.
Drive. Continue down MLK Drive (about a block). Elk Glen Picnic Area
will be on the right hand side, and Mallard Lake will be on the left.

 =46rom Golden Gate Bridge: After crossing the Golden Gate Bridge, take =20=

the
19th Avenue exit. Follow Park Presidio into Golden Gate Park. Continue
around Crossover drive to Martin Luther King Jr. Drive. Make a right on
MLK Drive. Continue down MLK Drive (about a block past 25th Avenue). Elk
Glen Picnic Area will be on the right hand side, and Mallard Lake will
be on the left.

 =46rom Hwy 280: Take 280 North to the 19th Avenue/Junipero Serra Blvd
Exit. Continue on 19th Ave until you pass between two large stone gates
(at the intersection of 19th Ave and Lincoln Way). After passing
straight through the 19th Ave/Lincoln intersection, look for signs
indicating the 25th Ave/Crossover Drive exit. Once exiting left on to
25th Ave, take the first available left turn onto Transverse Dr. Go
straight through the first stop sign (JFK Dr). At the next stop sign,
take a slight left (towards Martin Luther King Jr Drive). At the next
stop sign, take a right onto MLK Drive. Continue up MLK Drive. Elk
Glen Picnic Area will be on the right hand side, and Mallard Lake will
be on the left hand side.

Greetings, Folks!

I have expanded this invitation to participate in the Farmers Market  
Project and the Free Food Stand to other local lists, who may have a  
desire or need for either or who want to do something similar in their  
neighborhood, or who have done something similar and can give us  
tips...!

Forgive the delay on the follow-up for the Haight-Ashbury/Golden Gate  
Park Farmers Market Project. The soonest I can go full-steam on this  
project is July--my calendar is relatively open July and August  
(except for the farm and cottage being built--no other commitments, no  
guests!), and I want to give this project first dibs. So, I would like  
to propose that all those interested in taking an organizational lead-- 
great or small (there were a half dozen of us! BUT MORE ARE WELCOME!)-- 
to make this highly needed and historical thing happen--meet in early  
July: The Second Week, since people will have plans for the 4th.  
Pulling a date out of the hat--how about...

TUESDAY, JULY 8, 2008 ???
6:30pm ???
252 Frederick (corner of Downey) ???
Potluck  ???

If any committed people cannot make this date or time, or have a  
preferred place to meet, PLEASE LET ME KNOW OFF-LIST, and I will  
propose an update to the list to accommodate you!!!

***Heartfelt Congrats to Tree on his wonderful FREE FOOD STAND in the  
Mission--the photos and text at the web site are terrific,  
BEAUTIFUL!!! In case some of you have not seen this, check it out www.freefarmstand.org

Peace and Blessings!

Mary

Friday, May 30th
@ Anu, 43 6th St. @ Market, SF

FREE before 11pm,  $5 after.

Forest Green - 10pm to 12am
Developer - 12am to 1am
Drumcell - 1am to 2am

FAKTION is every Last Friday @ Anu

DRUMCELL: Droid Behavior/Omniscient [ LA ]
DEVELOPER: Modularz/Sound Division [ LA ]
FOREST GREEN: www.myspace.com/forestgreen
Cute Fang Recordings / Cute Things With Fangs, Daly
City Records , www.ForestGreen.org , Faktion [ SF ]

On their return from DEMF, Guadalajara Mexico and
great parties unknown, FAKTION brings you another
great lineup. Yes, we've really got DRUMCELL coming
here to help get you moving on the dance floor!
Recently, he and DJ DEVELOPER have been touring
together, representing LA Techno the world over, and
they've decided to drop by together for some fun in
San Francisco. As if these SoCal powerhouses weren't
enough, our own FOREST GREEN appears for some eclectic
techno spins of her own!

DRUMCELL: Founder of Droid Recordings and co-founder
of LA's Droid Behavior with Acid Circus, Drumcell's
energetic and frenetic take on minimal put LA on the
global map and always wins crowds over. He's played
all over the world and remains the standard bearer for
techno in Southern California.

DEVELOPER: DJ Developer is known throughout the US,
Mexico and abroad for quick mixing abilities and for
leading LA's second wave of Techno. Most recently, he
and longtime friend Drumcell have been touring
together, just like they're doing right here for you.

FOREST GREEN: In the bleakest days of San Francisco
techno, you could always count on Forest to bring out
totally dope techno, whether in a mainstream setting,
undergrounds or any other place in the world. Sure,
she's got the talent to pay the bills with balls-out
electro, breaks, dubstep beats, and nearly anything
else, she's also got the heart to consistently deliver
techno madness. We have no idea what she'll play or if
she'll pull out vinyl, cd, or even jam a live set,
we're just sure we'll love it and so will you!

Anu-Bar 43 Sixth St., San Francisco, CA 10 PM to 2 AM
21+ Cost: $5, free b4 11pm, LADIES FREE B4 MIDNIGHT!!!

Official Site: www.faktionsf.com/

* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *
* * * * * * * * * * *


///Radio Integrated :: radiointegrated@gmail.com ::
http://radio.defsf.com:1200/  ::   www.myspace.com/radiointegrated

Subject: [sfraves] BSP - Tonight on Radio Integrated... Live from Faktion with Drumcell, Developer, Forest Green

Tonight, Radio Integrated broadcasts live from Faktion at Anu! Come down and
meet us at 43 6th St if you're in San Francisco, otherwise tune in and we'll
bring the party to you.
For more information, check out Faktion at http://www.faktionsf.com .
Featuring sets from : : :

Drumcell  <http://www.defsf.com/radiointegrated/people/drumcell>(Droid
Behavior, LA)
Developer  <http://www.myspace.com/djdeveloper>(Modularz, LA)
Forest Green <http://www.myspace.com/forestgreen> (Cute Things With Fangs,
Daily City Records, ForestGreen.org
<http://www.forestgreen.org/><http://www.forestgreen.org/>,
SF)

Tune in at :

http://radio.defsf.com:1200/

>From 10pm-2am Pacific time.

***And by the way.... Next Friday is Get Integrated! An intimate techno loft
party brought to you by DEF and Radio Integrated.
Featuring Mattski, dCOY, James Bass, DJ STML, Chel-C Faith, and Disconnect.
Come party with us at Integrated HQ! Located in the East Bay, 5 minutes from
Downtown Oakland.
10pm-5am, $5 . . . More info at: www.defsf.com/getintegrated


More info regarding Faktion below....

* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *
* * * * * * * * * * *
F A K T I O N
Friday, May 30th
@ Anu, 43 6th St. @ Market, SF

FREE before 11pm,  $5 after.

Forest Green - 10pm to 12am
Developer - 12am to 1am
Drumcell - 1am to 2am

FAKTION is every Last Friday @ Anu

DRUMCELL: Droid Behavior/Omniscient [ LA ]
DEVELOPER: Modularz/Sound Division [ LA ]
FOREST GREEN: www.myspace.com/forestgreen
Cute Fang Recordings / Cute Things With Fangs, Daly
City Records , www.ForestGreen.org , Faktion [ SF ]

On their return from DEMF, Guadalajara Mexico and
great parties unknown, FAKTION brings you another
great lineup. Yes, we've really got DRUMCELL coming
here to help get you moving on the dance floor!
Recently, he and DJ DEVELOPER have been touring
together, representing LA Techno the world over, and
they've decided to drop by together for some fun in
San Francisco. As if these SoCal powerhouses weren't
enough, our own FOREST GREEN appears for some eclectic
techno spins of her own!

DRUMCELL: Founder of Droid Recordings and co-founder
of LA's Droid Behavior with Acid Circus, Drumcell's
energetic and frenetic take on minimal put LA on the
global map and always wins crowds over. He's played
all over the world and remains the standard bearer for
techno in Southern California.

DEVELOPER: DJ Developer is known throughout the US,
Mexico and abroad for quick mixing abilities and for
leading LA's second wave of Techno. Most recently, he
and longtime friend Drumcell have been touring
together, just like they're doing right here for you.

FOREST GREEN: In the bleakest days of San Francisco
techno, you could always count on Forest to bring out
totally dope techno, whether in a mainstream setting,
undergrounds or any other place in the world. Sure,
she's got the talent to pay the bills with balls-out
electro, breaks, dubstep beats, and nearly anything
else, she's also got the heart to consistently deliver
techno madness. We have no idea what she'll play or if
she'll pull out vinyl, cd, or even jam a live set,
we're just sure we'll love it and so will you!

Anu-Bar 43 Sixth St., San Francisco, CA 10 PM to 2 AM
21+ Cost: $5, free b4 11pm, LADIES FREE B4 MIDNIGHT!!!

Official Site: www.faktionsf.com/

* * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *
* * * * * * * * * * *

Subject: [sfraves] WR so far.... Friday Night Mondo Adventure!!!!

OK... so it's like hella early like right now now Satu Morning & I just
got home like a few minutes ago from my commute from the City & I shuld be
like hella goin' night night now, but this lil gypsy raver adventure I
had, i wanted to be able to post the details of it while still fresh in my
mind :)

OK.. so like my Lil Sis is home this weekend from NYC... last weekend was
older Sis... but yeah... so Lil Sis was goin' to the City, so I luckily
hitched a ride to Club 6 'cause I was kinda workin' there lastnight
kinda... like Legend Mag.. we had party there lastnight... it was a media
mixed/ art show/ 3 rooms of music including a live hip hop band that
well.. they did alota covers of ald skool rap songs, but broke up the
lyrics into like 5 people spitting which was kinda Dope I guess... but
yeah... it was fun.. there was alota free clothing shwag.. & we even had a
live photobooth photographer :)  In the main room, where the art show was,
there was like hip hop, breaks, & alota top 40 club booty, & down stairs
were my peoples spinning Audio1, Eva, & Kozzee & they dropped alota yummy
dubstep & some raga...

It was a really fun party... i'm guesstimating like a lil over like
somewhere around 150-180 people showed.. maybe almost kinda 200 'cause I
realized it was just like a stop over for hella people.. but oh man.. good
good yummy energy!!  It was Dope 'cause I bump3d into soooo many old skool
faces who I ain't seen for a reeeally fuckin' long time & it was also
kinda funny how ummmm... well.. a few people kinda knew who i was too &
lol... man... that was kinda random & hella made me LOL 4 hella long :)

OK... so well.. I like had to go in & out to like do last minute street
promotions & well... instead of flyering on Folsum, i went to Metreon &
the shops on Mission.. endedup getting brain freeze in the process 'cause
i hella piged out on free frozen yogart... anywaze... I ended getting
alota people from Anu to check it out 'cause well.. it was like right
there & I wanted I need techno so bad!!!  But wheni finally got off shift
@ 1AM, i spent the rest of my time @ Anu... I was on ly really able to
like really full get ummm.. what's his name.. DrumCells whole set.. 'cause
early in the night i only heard a small chunk of Forest... but yeah...
DrumCell like I dunno..

He started out playin', what i called, Tra La La Techno 'cause I mean.. it
coulda been minimal i guess.. but it was just sooooo Tra La La the way it
sounded & it was kinda to not yummy for me to dance to & I sooo could not
get into it.. Hello 2Day.. then he progre3ssive got into kinda harder
bouncy stuff that i was diggin' & I danced out maybe the last 20 minutes
of the club... It was kinda fun 'cause after Anu closed & Ray was fixing
the decks & mixer up to like when we all ended up in the parking lot, like
DrumCell & I kinda caught up on everything since we last hung out last
year... So dope.. he always says somethiung inspiring to me whenever we
talk & stuff... so that was kinda CooL...

So Ray dropped me off @ like what was suppose to be this underground by
12th & Folsum, but it was just the back room of Studio Z... had no money
to get in... so i jsut went to AllStar on 5th for a donut & coffee... ok..
so here's where the raver gypsy adventure gets like even more fun,
adventurous, interesting, & some kinda strangeness in there too!  This
almost kinda dragqueen walks in, orders food, & we end up talking 'cause
he was giving the dude behind the counter like this hard time in a queeny
way & I hella laughed 'cause she was funny!  Her name is ummm
Wristflipper, ummm.... Wrist Clicker... no no no.. wait.. ummm...
LIMPWRIST! WE both finished our food then she decided to help me kill time
& walk around 'til BART opened... other than having an hours worth of
conversation, we also ended up going to a sex club that was closed 'cause
people left early...

After i walked Limpwrist 1/2 back to her hotel, I saw 1 of them sweeper
dudes that clean up the trash around BART (Civic Center Station) & him & I
end up talking for a few minutes while he was cleaning.. I asked him if
the water people were coming to wet down the station like they do every
morning & Thankfully they didn't!  But yeah... this guy waws hella funny &
he had this really weird accent, like it sounded like he was from
Brooklyn, NY, but now so much... then he told me he was German & then it
made sense that he had this German Accent mixed with a Brooklyn Accent &
yeah.... this guy, Peter, was just heeeeeeeella fuckin' funny!!!

Then I went down in the lower part by the stairs towards the entrance to
BART & the Escalators... some dude was there I thoght fixing it... but he
cleaned it & I've never seen an escalator look that clean, I wanted to
like lick it... anywaze... his name is Rob, he lives in Portland w/ his
family & has 3 jobs... an escalator cleaner, an elevator parts person, & a
lumberjack... I guess he's the best Elevator cleaner for the City to get
him out here to Clean & fix Escalators... but yeah... Peter joined us down
by the excalators & the 3 of started naming the rats that were running
around!  LoL.. Hello 2day!!

OK... but yeah... with just 1/2 an hour to go, i was just getting happy
that bart was almost open... then this homeless dude, Crack Head Gary, who
i met over a year ago calls me & well.. he wanted to like catch up & guess
& talk... like the last time we "hung out", he just got outta the hospital
& still had his braclets on & something... so we ended up walk a ways into
the TL & I swear man.. this Dude's like the king of the Homeless crack
heads 'cause the other crackheads were like givin' him alota like biggups
when we walked through... it was kinda funny... we we chatted, caught up,
& luckily I got back to BART just as the 1st train to the East Bay pulled
up!   Probably woulda got home alot sooner if that Newbie bus driver knew
how to drive a bus... but whatev...

OK... night night SFR... i <3 U!



-- 
Take Care <3
Peace=->Jus' Me =-> ObY {8O)


oooh.. PS Greg... I need the info again.. I Lost the flyer :(

> > City Records , www.ForestGreen.org , Faktion [ SF ]
> > 
> > On their return from DEMF, Guadalajara Mexico and
> > great parties unknown, FAKTION brings you another
> > great lineup. Yes, we've really got DRUMCELL coming
> > here to help get you moving on the dance floor!
> > Recently, he and DJ DEVELOPER have been touring
> > together, representing LA Techno the world over, and
> > they've decided to drop by together for some fun in
> > San Francisco. As if these SoCal powerhouses weren't
> > enough, our own FOREST GREEN appears for some eclectic
> > techno spins of her own!
> > 
> > DRUMCELL: Founder of Droid Recordings and co-founder
> > of LA's Droid Behavior with Acid Circus, Drumcell's
> > energetic and frenetic take on minimal put LA on the
> > global map and always wins crowds over. He's played
> > all over the world and remains the standard bearer for
> > techno in Southern California.
> > 
> > DEVELOPER: DJ Developer is known throughout the US,
> > Mexico and abroad for quick mixing abilities and for
> > leading LA's second wave of Techno. Most recently, he
> > and longtime friend Drumcell have been touring
> > together, just like they're doing right here for you.
> > 
> > FOREST GREEN: In the bleakest days of San Francisco
> > techno, you could always count on Forest to bring out
> > totally dope techno, whether in a mainstream setting,
> > undergrounds or any other place in the world. Sure,
> > she's got the talent to pay the bills with balls-out
> > electro, breaks, dubstep beats, and nearly anything
> > else, she's also got the heart to consistently deliver
> > techno madness. We have no idea what she'll play or if
> > she'll pull out vinyl, cd, or even jam a live set,
> > we're just sure we'll love it and so will you!
> > 
> > Anu-Bar 43 Sixth St., San Francisco, CA 10 PM to 2 AM
> > 21+ Cost: $5, free b4 11pm, LADIES FREE B4 MIDNIGHT!!!

>>> techno spins of her own!

>>> of LA's Droid Behavior with Acid Circus, Drumcell's
>>> energetic and frenetic take on minimal put LA on the
>>> global map and always wins crowds over. He's played
>>> all over the world and remains the standard bearer for
>>> techno in Southern California.
>>>
>>> DEVELOPER: DJ Developer is known throughout the US,
>>> Mexico and abroad for quick mixing abilities and for
>>> leading LA's second wave of Techno. Most recently, he
>>> and longtime friend Drumcell have been touring
>>> together, just like they're doing right here for you.
>>>
>>> FOREST GREEN: In the bleakest days of San Francisco
>>> techno, you could always count on Forest to bring out
>>> totally dope techno, whether in a mainstream setting,
>>> undergrounds or any other place in the world. Sure,
>>> she's got the talent to pay the bills with balls-out
>>> electro, breaks, dubstep beats, and nearly anything
>>> else, she's also got the heart to consistently deliver
>>> techno madness. We have no idea what she'll play or if
>>> she'll pull out vinyl, cd, or even jam a live set,
>>> we're just sure we'll love it and so will you!

Super Heroes on Vacation

Tonight, May 31st, Camp !Zoom! (aka The Bunnyjam Krew!) will be 
bringing a little bit of the Playa to the concrete jungle as they host a 
camp benefit at The Oasis in Oakland (135 12th St. in Oakland.) Music 
starts at 9p and goes until 2a. As many of you don't need an excuse to 
break out your best costumes, I'm expecting to see some lots of creative 
interpretations of the theme!

9pm-2am
$10 (Pssst - $5 in Costume)
21+

Dancing - Art - Fire

Food available until midnight

Performances by the Fire Arts Collective

Dance music by DJs:
J.C. (KZSU, camp HOTD)
Lord Kook (FSLD, camp Zombie Pixels)
NeonBunny (dish, camp !Zoom!)

Downtempo and Ambient Grooves by DJs:
Pepe Mapache (Guadalajara, Mexico)
Mak (Hotel W's famous Friday Happy Hour)
Xan-X (Ambi-Sonic)

Sculptures and Installations by Starboy & Cary; NeonBunny

More details here: http://neonbunny.com/events.html

Hope to see you out there!
